🔤 1. Strings in Python

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 What is a String?

```text id="string_def2"
A string is a sequence of characters enclosed in quotes.
````

---

💻 String Example

```python id="string_example2"
name = "Python"

print(name)
print(type(name))
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="string_output2"
Python
<class 'str'>
```

---

🔤 String Indexing

Each character has an index position.

---

💻 Example

```python id="string_indexing"
word = "Python"

print(word[0])
print(word[1])
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="string_index_output"
P
y
```

---

🔄 String Slicing

Used to extract parts of a string.

---

💻 Example

```python id="string_slicing"
text = "Programming"

print(text[0:6])
print(text[3:])
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="string_slice_output"
Progra
gramming
```

---

🔧 Common String Methods

| Method      | Purpose              |
| ----------- | -------------------- |
| `upper()`   | Convert to uppercase |
| `lower()`   | Convert to lowercase |
| `strip()`   | Remove spaces        |
| `replace()` | Replace text         |
| `split()`   | Split string         |

---

💻 Example

```python id="string_methods"
message = " hello python "

print(message.upper())
print(message.strip())
print(message.replace("python", "world"))
```

